    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-12-12T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-12-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="574" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d574">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Webb</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 13.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-12-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">December</hi> 12, 1861.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I recur to your despatch (No. 3) of the
                            date of October 24.</p>
                <p>Your course in issuing your circular, concerning the secession flag, to
                            the consuls in the Brazilian empire is approved. We trust that it will
                            have the effect of saving the national prestige in South America.</p>
                <p>It is to be regretted that the late minister—your predecessor—and the
                            late <pb facs="0774" n="704" xml:id="pg_704"/> consul at Rio have
                            probably escaped, for the present, the account which they owe to the
                            government for their treasonable abuse of the confidence of their
                            country.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James Watson Webb,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
